> Full Gherkin reference is in `docs/atdd/gherkin.md`. Key rules summarized below.

## File Location & Naming

- All `.feature` files go in `specs/features/`
- Names use `kebab-case.feature`
- One feature per file

## Tags

| Tag           | Meaning                                        | Count     |
| ------------- | ---------------------------------------------- | --------- |
| `@smoke`      | Single most critical path                      | Exactly 1 |
| `@happy-path` | Primary success flows                          | 1–2       |
| `@edge-case`  | Boundary conditions                            | 2–4       |
| `@error`      | Invalid inputs, auth failures, system failures | 2–3       |
| `@wip`        | Not yet implemented                            | Temporary |

## Step Rules

- **Given** — state/context, never an action
- **When** — the action or event being tested (one per scenario)
- **Then** — observable outcome from user/caller perspective, never internal state
- Use `And` / `But` for additional steps of the same type

## Formatting

- 2-space indent inside `Feature:`, `Background:`, `Scenario:`
- Blank line between scenarios
- String literals in double quotes: `"expected text"`
- Scenario Outline variables in angle brackets: `<variable_name>`

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid

- Multiple `When` steps — split into separate scenarios
- `Then` asserting DB state or internal calls — assert via observable behavior
- Vague `Then`: `"Then it should work"` — specify exact observable outcome with concrete values
- Scenario depending on state from another scenario — use Background or explicit Given steps
